      "writtenOn": "2026-07-23T15:54:44Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Querying subordinate resources kind of has the same issue of possible misconfiguration and out-of-spec.\n\nIf two chassis \u0027own\u0027 a fan on D-Bus it\u0027s out of spec in redfish and we should not return any out-of-spec responses.\nBy using the other mapper calls this full picture is not available. I did not really handle this case in my implementation but at least with a bigger mapper call choices would have been available for anyone willing to tackle it.\n\nAnyways that\u0027s just how it works for now i guess. I changed it to use the original `getFanPaths()` call for the owned fans as suggested.",
      "parentUuid": "cd8f64c8_6d30ab54",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 157,
        "startChar": 1,
        "endLine": 175,
        "endChar": 1
